article.headline: Portland 79, CS Bakersfield 76
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Nik Raivio scored nine of his 33 points in overtime and Portland beat Cal State Bakersfield 79-76 Tuesday. Portland (8-6) never trailed in overtime and led by as many as 10 points in the second half before the Roadrunners rallied to force the extra period. Raivio was 7-for-8 from the free-throw line in overtime. Alex Johnson led Bakersfield (4-10) with 23 points, while Santwon Latunde scored 15 points and Donavan Bragg added 14 points. Bakersfield led 31-30 at halftime but Portland went on a 15-6 run to lead 47-37 at the 13:12 mark. The Roadrunners rallied down the stretch, and Bragg's jumper with 1:17 gave them a brief lead. Jaren Stohl's 3 with 44 seconds sent the game to overtime. Stohl scored 17.
